get.description: This endpoint allows you to retrieve balance tied to a particular address on a specific chain.The response of this API will let you understand in details about all your assets.

**The token transactions API fetches the list of all transactions in wallet address**

Our Bank statements often let us understand the financial positions of a bank account. Similarly for a Crypto wallet , the transactions gives the wallet holder a detailed analysis of the inbound and out bound transfers thereby keeping the wallet apprised of all the happenings in their wallet. 

Unmarshal Transaction APIs are smart enough to differentiate the kind of operation a particular transaction was made for. It will let a user understand if the transaction was  was for a send or receive or the amount was staked or un-staked , or if the transactions was for adding or removing liquidity .

**The token transactions API fetches the list of all transactions in wallet address**

Our Bank statements often let us understand the financial positions of a bank account. Similarly for a Crypto wallet, the transactions gives the wallet holder a detailed analysis of the inbound and out bound transfers thereby keeping the wallet apprised of all the happenings in their wallet. 

Unmarshal Transaction APIs are smart enough to differentiate the kind of operation a particular transaction was made for. It will let a user understand if the transaction was  was for a send or receive or the amount was staked or un-staked , or if the transactions was for adding or removing liquidity .

The transaction detail API is one such End Point which gives as much details possible for a specific transaction on a specific given chain.

 
All we need is the transaction hash and the entire history of the transaction is presented to anyone looking for all minor details pertaining to the particular transaction
NFT assets API gives the information about all the NFT assets held by a address on BSC and ethereum chain.
NFT transactions API gives the list of transaction being made on given wallet address.

get.description: This api provides price of token by taking the symbol of the token(ticker) as a parameter which will give latest price, timestamp can also be provided as a query param to get historical data.

This api provides price of a token by taking the address of the token(contract of token) in any chain such as Ethereum, Matic and Binance, timestamp can be provided as a query parameter to view historical data.

get.summary: Get Price for multiple Token Addresses
get.description: This api takes multiple contract addresses to provide price data at once, timestamp can be provided as a query parameter to view historical data. multiple contracts have to given in comma(,) separated.
API provides a list of top gainers in a particular chain. the data contains biggest gainers in last 24 hours.
API provides a list of top losers in a particular chain. the data contains biggest losers in last 24 hours.
This api provides the price for LP tokens by taking in the address of the Lp tokens.
when searched by token contract address, it fetches exhaustive information of the token.
when searched with the ticker name of any token, it returns detailed information of the token within the blockchains it exists in.
when searched with string “list”, it pulls the list of all the tokens that exist on Ethereum, BSC and Polygon
This endpoint will return top-traders for a given pair.

tags.name: NFTs
tags.description: NFTs the latest buzz in the crypto world and Unmarshal is there to support with the data needs around NFTs as well.

tags.name: Price Store
tags.description:
Pricestore API contains endpoints that provide the latest price of a token as well as historical price of the tokens, these tokens can also be LP tokens. Tokens supported from ETH/BSC/Matic chains
These api's also provide top losers and gainers.

tags.name: Token Store
tags.description:
With data of more than 100,000+ tokens, Token Store is one of the finest products when it comes to querying token attributes; either with the contract address of the token or with the token ticker itself. This gives developers the flexibility and ease of querying data in more than one way with just a single line of code.
The details fetched by the product is comprehensive along with granular information. The distinctive data fetched for every query through Token Store:
“Symbol”, “Contract”, “Logo”, “Decimal”, “Blockchain”, “Website”, “Total Supply”, "Verified" and “Explorer”
Verified flag returns the status of token. if its a valid token we return true, else returns false.
